

Scanner Class: used fot getting inputs
               needs to be imported from "java.util"

               *First:Import
               syntex of import statement:
                          import package.class;
                          import java.util.Scanner;  (use this generally)
               *Second: Sout Enter bla bla for user to understand
               *Third: Declare
                       Scanner variableName = new Scanner(System.in);

               *Fourth: Scanner Methods
                    int num= variableName.nextInt();

               *Fifth:     than
                    *String result = ""; //temporary
                    *if
                    sout result

               *Last: Closing
               variablename.close();


       Boolean= nextBoolean();  user input olarak sadece true or false yazabilir
       String =    next();   one word input.tek kelime ise(kelimeler arası bosluksuz yazarsan da olur)
                   nextLine();  reads everything until press enter. birden fazla kelime, normal yazı ise

           ** nextLine(); if we are using nextLine() method after the other methods of scanner, we must provide
           one addition nextLine();     -> to clear scanner
           when you use nextLine method after the other methods of scanner
           it is ignore enter key, to avoid ignoring enter key we should add input.nextLine(); before nextline

           nextInt method
           input.nextLine(); (for enter)
           nextline method